olive oil
½ unit carrot
1 clove garlic
1 unit tomato
1 unit cucumber
1 bag baby spinach leaves
½ unit lemon
1 bunch mint
20 g butter
¾ cup water (for the couscous)
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 packet couscous
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
½ tsp water (for the sauce)

Grate the carrot (see ingredients list), unpeeled. Finely chop the garlic (or use a garlic press). Roughly chop the tomato and cucumber. Roughly chop the baby spinach leaves. Zest the lemon (see ingredients list) to get a pinch, then slice into wedges. Pick and roughly chop the mint leaves.

In a medium saucepan, melt the butter with a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Add the carrot and cook, stirring, until softened, 2-3 minutes. Add the garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute. Add the water (for the couscous) and vegetable stock. Bring to the boil. Add the couscous, stir to combine, then cover with a lid and remove from the heat. Set aside until the water is absorbed, 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork and set aside, uncovered.

While the couscous is cooking, slice the pork loin steaks into 0.5cm strips. In a large bowl combine the chermoula spice blend, yoghurt (1 tbs for 2 people / 2 tbs for 4 people), a squeeze of lemon juice and drizzle of olive oil. Add the pork strips and toss to coat.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a high heat. Add 1/2 the pork strips and cook, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a plate and repeat with the remaining pork.

In a small bowl, combine the remaining yoghurt, water (for the sauce), a pinch of salt and pepper and a drizzle of olive oil. Set aside. In a large bowl, combine the carrot couscous, lemon zest, tomato, cucumber, baby spinach and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide the carrot couscous and tomato salad between plates. Top with the chermoula pork strips. Drizzle with the yoghurt and garnish with the mint. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges.